headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored a season-high 45 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Brooklyn Nets 111-102 on Thursday in the NBA's third regular-season game in Paris.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores season-high 45 points, Cavaliers beat Nets 111-102 in Paris

headlines.description: — Facing the NBA-leading Boston Celtics got the Milwaukee Bucks to break out of their slump and deliver their most dominating performance of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portis, Antetokounmpo spark 25-0 spurt in Bucks' 135-102 blowout of Celtics

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points, Josh Giddey had a triple-double and the Oklahoma City Thunder rolled past the Portland Trail Blazers 139-77 on Thursday night, a 62-point victory that matched the fifth-largest rout in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder roll past Trail Blazers 139-77, tie fifth-biggest victory margin in NBA history

events.name: New York Knicks at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored a season-high 44 points, Tim Hardaway Jr. added 32 in his fifth start of the season and the short-handed Dallas Mavericks, playing without superstar Luka Doncic and two other starters, held off a late charge to beat the New York...
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 44, Hardaway Jr. 32 as Luka-less Mavericks beat Knicks 128-124

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Frank Vogel and Kevin Durant had some goals before the Phoenix Suns faced the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley Beal scores 37, Devin Booker adds 31 as Suns roll to a 127-109 victory over Lakers
